docs {
  # List Pareto Curves

  Returns all Pareto curve definitions. Each curve represents a performance frontier for a submission.

  ## Data Shape

  ```json
  [
    {
      "id": "pareto-001",
      "submissionId": "sub-001",
      "systemId": "system1",
      "description": "System 1 - DeepSeek R1 Pareto frontier",
      "minConcurrency": 1,
      "maxConcurrency": 64
    }
  ]
  ```

  ## Fields

  | Field | Type | Description |
  |-------|------|-------------|
  | id | string | Unique pareto curve identifier |
  | submissionId | string | Reference to submission |
  | systemId | string | Reference to system |
  | description | string | Human-readable description |
  | minConcurrency | number | Minimum concurrent users tested |
  | maxConcurrency | number | Maximum concurrent users tested |

  ## Relationships

  - Links to `submissions` via `submissionId`
  - Links to `systems` via `systemId`
  - Referenced by `dataPoints` via `paretoCurveId`

  ## Filter Examples

  - `?systemId=system1` - Curves for a specific system
  - `?submissionId=sub-001` - Curve for a specific submission
}
